introduction.text: In Queensland, where my next song originated, during the Dry season the river beds can be used as natural roads to drive cattle from the huge farms – or “Stations” such as “Old Cork Station” mentioned in the song, down to where the grass is greener, down by NSW and the markets of the city. This song tells the story of an old drover, driving herds of cattle on the hoof,  along the dried-up river-bed of the Diamantina River, realizing he’ll never move back to the city, that this is the life for him despite its hardship.  Ladies and gentlemen: The Diamantina Drover
